01:55.494 --> 01:57.462
- The sign says "The Big Bang."

01:57.496 --> 02:00.672
- [continues speaking
in foreign language]

02:00.706 --> 02:02.639
♪

02:02.674 --> 02:05.539
- Okay, so when the world was--
when the universe was created,

02:05.573 --> 02:08.369
um, the universe is like
an egg...

02:08.404 --> 02:09.888
- Eggs.
- That broke.

02:09.922 --> 02:11.165
- Yes.
- Okay?

02:11.200 --> 02:13.478
From the shell...
- Yes.

02:13.512 --> 02:15.652
- Is this fellow here.
He's called [indistinct].

02:15.687 --> 02:17.344
- Yes.
- From the yellow...

02:17.378 --> 02:19.173
- Yes.
- The yolk...

02:19.208 --> 02:20.485
- [speaking native language]
- The--the teacher...

02:20.519 --> 02:21.831
- Yes.
- [speaking native language]

02:21.865 --> 02:23.384
- The teacher.
- And then they put

02:23.419 --> 02:25.179
the white...
- And the white of the egg

02:25.214 --> 02:28.182
is Semar.

02:28.217 --> 02:30.840
- [speaking native language]

02:30.874 --> 02:32.255
- Semar?
- Yes.

02:32.290 --> 02:34.671
- Is to accompany the good.

02:34.706 --> 02:38.572
So this is to accompany
the bad, the demon.

02:38.606 --> 02:40.574
This is to accompany the good.

02:40.608 --> 02:43.232
- So the philosophy is,
without this,

02:43.266 --> 02:44.578
there is no this.

02:44.612 --> 02:47.201
Without this,
there is not this.

02:47.236 --> 02:49.479
- There is no right
without wrong.

02:49.514 --> 02:51.688
There is no dark without light,

02:51.723 --> 02:54.243
but each interconnects.

02:54.277 --> 02:56.693
- Yes.
- That is the main philosophy.

02:56.728 --> 02:59.524
You know, the existence comes

02:59.558 --> 03:01.698
from the same egg.

03:01.733 --> 03:04.908
[dramatic percussive music]

03:04.943 --> 03:11.984
♪

03:15.954 --> 03:18.715
- [singing in foreign language]

03:18.750 --> 03:21.718
- For a thousand years,
the Wayang--

03:21.753 --> 03:24.411
or shadow play--
has been entertainment

03:24.445 --> 03:27.241
for both mortals and the gods.

03:27.276 --> 03:29.243
♪

03:29.278 --> 03:30.555
In the shadow world,

03:30.589 --> 03:32.557
everything has its opposites.

03:32.591 --> 03:34.697
- [singing in foreign language]

03:34.731 --> 03:38.356
- At worth within every man
are forces both divine

03:38.390 --> 03:39.874
and animalistic.

03:39.909 --> 03:42.256
- [vocalizing]

03:42.291 --> 03:44.431
- The philosophy
of the shadow play

03:44.465 --> 03:46.743
is to strive for balance.

03:46.778 --> 03:51.403
You cannot kill the dominant
animal urges within.

03:51.438 --> 03:53.440
You must harness them,

03:53.474 --> 03:56.270
yet not be controlled by them.

03:56.305 --> 03:58.410
- [man vocalizing]

03:58.445 --> 04:03.484
♪

04:03.519 --> 04:05.728
Shadows that manifest
on-screen

04:05.762 --> 04:07.730
are more than mere relief.

04:07.764 --> 04:10.905
As they come alive,
timeless tales

04:10.940 --> 04:13.770
interspersed with
subversive stories

04:13.805 --> 04:16.842
bring the world of gods,
monsters, and heroes

04:16.877 --> 04:20.398
into sync with current
social commentary.

04:20.432 --> 04:23.297
♪

04:23.332 --> 04:26.300
- [singing in foreign language]

04:26.335 --> 04:31.581
♪

04:31.616 --> 04:33.100
- Indonesia is--
correct me if I'm wrong--

04:33.134 --> 04:35.447
it's the fourth largest
country in the world.

04:35.482 --> 04:37.311
- The fourth largest,
but we are

04:37.346 --> 04:39.451
the third largest democracy.

04:39.486 --> 04:41.315
17,00 islands.

04:41.350 --> 04:44.387
The majority
of the population--60%--

04:44.422 --> 04:45.837
live on Java.

04:45.871 --> 04:47.839
- And how many people
in Jakarta?

04:47.873 --> 04:50.842
- Greater Jakarta,
there's around 25 million.

04:50.876 --> 04:52.430
- 25 million?
- 25--

04:52.464 --> 04:54.466
that's the greater area.

04:54.501 --> 04:59.609
♪

04:59.644 --> 05:01.335
- What should the rest
of the world know

05:01.370 --> 05:03.441
about the fourth-largest
country in the world

05:03.475 --> 05:04.476
that they don't know?

05:04.511 --> 05:07.341
Because, let's face it,

05:07.376 --> 05:09.136
I think if you asked
most people who are--

05:09.170 --> 05:11.552
who are gonna watch this show,
"Tell me something

05:11.587 --> 05:15.004
about Indonesia,"
you'll get a total blank.

05:15.038 --> 05:18.801
- Indonesia,
we are very, very diverse

05:18.835 --> 05:20.699
because even before Islam came,

05:20.734 --> 05:23.426
the locals,
they had their own traditions.

05:23.461 --> 05:26.049
They have their own culture.
- [speaking native language]

05:26.084 --> 05:27.810
Tolerance...
- The tolerance...

05:27.844 --> 05:30.053
The tolerance, uh, the--
the attitude of tolerance--

05:30.088 --> 05:33.643
religion tolerance--
uh, that drop in our country.

05:33.678 --> 05:36.405
- Uh, the--the level
of tolerance is declining.

05:36.439 --> 05:39.062
- Yes, but in the food...

05:43.619 --> 05:45.414
- Basically, food is
a great unifier.

05:45.448 --> 05:46.863
- Right.
- You see?

05:46.898 --> 05:48.658
Especially in the...
- You may speak poorly

05:48.693 --> 05:50.591
of another region--
"Oh, they're terrible people

05:50.626 --> 05:52.490
over there, but their food
is good."

05:52.524 --> 05:54.112
- Yep.
They say that if

05:54.146 --> 05:57.391
you really want to know
and try every single dish

05:57.426 --> 06:00.601
in Indonesia, you have
to live here for 40 years.

06:00.636 --> 06:03.397
- 40 years.
- You need to stay here

06:03.432 --> 06:04.467
for a long time,

06:04.502 --> 06:07.539
because every single area

06:07.574 --> 06:10.404
has its own specialty.

06:10.439 --> 06:13.407
[rousing percussive music]

06:13.442 --> 06:20.483
♪

06:22.209 --> 06:25.212
Padang food--
this is from West Sumatra.

06:25.246 --> 06:28.595
If we talk about fast food,
this is the fastest food.

06:28.629 --> 06:30.113
I mean, this is way before

06:30.148 --> 06:33.565
this genre of fast-foot
exist in the world.

06:33.600 --> 06:35.636
♪

06:35.671 --> 06:37.431
As you sit down,
they come up with

06:37.466 --> 06:38.984
all the dishes,
and the concept is

06:39.019 --> 06:41.918
you choose what you want
to eat, and you only pay...

06:41.953 --> 06:44.127
- Right.
- For what you want to eat.

06:44.162 --> 06:46.716
Here is...
- [speaking native language]

06:46.751 --> 06:48.097
- It's lungs.
Fried lungs.

06:48.131 --> 06:49.547
- Lung, lung.
both: Fried lungs.

06:49.581 --> 06:51.997
- This is an
intestine goulash,

06:52.032 --> 06:54.621
and this--basically the skin.

06:54.655 --> 06:56.588
- Deep fried fat and skin,
yep.

06:56.623 --> 06:57.934
Oh, I like that.

06:57.969 --> 06:59.557
- Of course this is rendang.

06:59.591 --> 07:01.800
We're very fond of our rendang.

07:01.835 --> 07:04.941
And what makes Padang food
very special

07:04.976 --> 07:06.253
is the spice.
- Yes.

07:06.287 --> 07:09.187
- The spice and the chili.

07:09.221 --> 07:11.189
♪

07:11.223 --> 07:12.570
- So good.

07:12.604 --> 07:14.779
- Yeah, you like rendang?
- I do.

07:14.813 --> 07:17.506
I could eat that all day.

07:17.540 --> 07:19.508
♪

07:19.542 --> 07:22.027
So, I--I wanted to ask,

07:22.062 --> 07:25.755
the traditional Indonesian
shadow play...

07:25.790 --> 07:26.963
how does one learn?

07:26.998 --> 07:29.483
How did you, uh,
learn your art?

07:29.518 --> 07:32.521
- All shadow-puppet masters...
[speaking native language]

07:32.555 --> 07:35.006
- Yes, it's all, you know,
passed on from generation

07:35.040 --> 07:36.973
to generation.
- So your father did this

07:37.008 --> 07:37.871
as well.

07:37.905 --> 07:40.494
And as I understand it,
traditionally...

07:40.529 --> 07:42.876
the puppet-master was allowed

07:42.910 --> 07:46.017
a certain latitude to...

07:46.051 --> 07:47.846
tease, provoke,

07:47.881 --> 07:51.160
or openly mock the powerful.

07:51.194 --> 07:53.127
How far can you go?

07:53.162 --> 07:55.682
- It's a bit like
in the court jester...

07:55.716 --> 07:57.822
- Right.
- Where the court jesters

07:57.856 --> 07:59.651
are expected...

07:59.686 --> 08:01.688
you know,
to make people laugh,

08:01.722 --> 08:04.000
but at the same time
it's an opportunity also

08:04.035 --> 08:05.623
to criticize...
- Mm-hmm.

08:05.657 --> 08:08.246
- Without getting...

08:08.280 --> 08:10.006
punished for it.

08:10.041 --> 08:12.906
But at the same time, there is
a philosophical level to it...

08:12.940 --> 08:15.667
- Mm-hmm.
- To make the people aware

08:15.702 --> 08:18.670
of certain dangers...
- Aware that...

08:18.705 --> 08:21.708
[speaking native language]

08:21.742 --> 08:25.021
- Yeah, so to make
the people aware that truth...

08:25.056 --> 08:27.541
- Mm-hmm.
- And wrong-doings is--

08:27.576 --> 08:29.336
it's actually not
black and white.

08:29.370 --> 08:31.234
They interconnect.

09:14.795 --> 09:15.900
[dramatic percussive music]

09:15.934 --> 09:17.902
- [speaking native language]

09:17.936 --> 09:19.731
- Watch the shadows,

09:19.766 --> 09:21.906
not the puppets.

09:21.940 --> 09:23.770
The right in constant struggle

09:23.804 --> 09:25.910
with the left.
- [singing in foreign language]

09:25.944 --> 09:28.119
- Forces of light
and darkness

09:28.153 --> 09:30.915
in an endless fight
for supremacy.

09:30.949 --> 09:32.813
Neither prevailing.

09:32.848 --> 09:35.920
- [singing in foreign language]

09:35.954 --> 09:38.232
- What is good?

09:38.267 --> 09:40.683
What is evil?

09:40.718 --> 09:41.926
Who is the hero?

09:41.960 --> 09:43.755
Who is the villain?

09:43.790 --> 09:45.654
What is up or down?

09:45.688 --> 09:46.413
Black or white?

09:46.447 --> 09:49.761
What is right or wrong?

09:49.796 --> 09:51.142
In shadow-play,

09:51.176 --> 09:54.628
no such final conclusion
exists.

09:54.663 --> 10:00.669
♪

